<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-52-0619 </DOCNO><TEXT>The invention refers to a device for positioning and rotating an elementin an irradiation channel. Inside an outer tube, coaxial pieces of tubeof different diameter are provided, where the adjacent ones can be movedinside one another and in the extended state grip one another at theirends in a form locking manner. A rotating drive acts on the top pieceof tube, while the lowest piece of tube can be connected in a form lockingmanner with the element.</TEXT></DOC>